item.title: Alphabet X spinoff partners with Arc’teryx to bring ‘everyday’ exoskeleton to market
item.description:
Skip, a wearable tech startup that began as a Google X project, exited stealth this week to announce a partnership with outdoor clothing specialist Arc’teryx. The deal is the first to bring Skip’s technology to market: “powered pants” that utilize a soft exoskeleton developed in-house at Alphabet’s X Labs moonshot factory. The tech, called MO/GO, […]
